    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Some references\n- http://matplotlib.org/1.3.1/users/transforms_tutorial.html\n- http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9103166/multiple-axis-in-matplotlib-with-different-scales\n- http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8230638/parallel-coordinates-plot-in-matplotlib\n- http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5656798/python-matplotlib-is-there-a-way-to-make-a-discontinuous-axis\n\nI haven't worked with matplotlib transforms much, but I think they're the best solution. The idea is to apply a transform to each coordinate independently (both the data and the scale). Right now we just fake the scale by drawing a `vline` at each coordinate, so that will have to be reworked.\n\nI'll look at this over the weekend, depending on how my other PRs come along.\n"
  },
